@flexiarg musn/off-trail-brief-log
@title Brief Off-Trail Logging
@sigils [üåè/ËÆ°]
@audience fulab agents, musn server
@tone technical
@style pattern

! conclusion: When going off-trail, keep the note brief and record why.
  + context: Off-trail actions are allowed but must be explainable.
  + IF:
    The agent goes off-trail without a reason or with long, unfocused justification.
  + HOWEVER:
    Exploration can be necessary for progress.
  + THEN:
    Log a short reason for off-trail actions (one sentence, anchored to intent).
  + BECAUSE:
    Brief reasons preserve auditability without derailing the run.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: turn/action note includes a concise off-trail rationale.
    - evidence-shape: {:action :string, :note :string, :on-trail :boolean}
